name: Fixing the health check
body: This release fixes the health check. The health check file now gets updated on every queue processed rather than on end of all queues.

name: Change default prefix to be empty, some readme and test cleanups
Remove Elastic Beanstalk support, Adding CircleCI build process
body: Remove Elastic Beanstalk support and grouping support, Adding CircleCI build process

name: re-fetch queue to cache in case of deletion
Prevent high CPU if there are no queues available for a worker
error handling and db management for signals
Improve log on re-queueing by SQS
Fix log on re-queueing by SQS
Django signals to expose the WorkerService progress
Proper Django DB handling
body: Fixes missing DB connection closing when max-live time has been specified and EB-SQS is run using the process_queue management command.

name: Refactoring to support better extendability
body:
- Refactor queue processing to support better extendability
- Bulk delete messages to improve performance

name: Support listening to a dynamic set of queues, using a prefix
body:
- support prefix notation, to listen to a dynamic set of queues
- support configuring message retention and visibility timeout on auto-created queues
- upgrading boto3 to the latest version

name: Python3 better support and boto version update
body:
- upgrading boto3 to the latest version
- adding boto3 sqs retry limit
- fixing python3 issues
- changing AUTO_ADD_QUEUE to be False by default (you should be explicit when you wish to create SQS queues)

name: Python3 compatible
body: This version is the first to support Python3.
